    "title": {
        "rendered": "MatR: Bruce Springsteen and Mike Ness: Bad Luck"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>If you were with me about six months ago, you may remember our spotlight on Bruce&#8217;s studio guest appearance with Mike Ness on &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/01/22/matr-mike-ness-and-bruce-springsteen-misery-loves-company/\">Misery Loves Company</a>.&#8221;</p>\n<p>I led that article stating that Bruce had been a fan of Social Distortion (Ness&#8217; band) since the early nineties. It&#8217;s a pretty safe bet that one of the songs that originally grabbed his attention was &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tQOJY4NXYzM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;Bad Luck&#8221; was the lead single for\u00a0<em>Somewhere Between Heaven and Hell</em>, Social Distortion&#8217;s fourth studio album in 1992. It quickly became&#8211;and remains&#8211;the band&#8217;s biggest hit, peaking at #2 on the Billboard Modern Rock Tracks (now known as Alternative Airplay) chart.</p>\n<p>Years later, Ness made two appearances with Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band, once on the Working on a Dream Tour and again on the Wrecking Ball Tour. On both occasions, the song they played together was Social Distortion&#8217;s biggest hit.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/d3irr_f-ZIs?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Six years after Ness&#8217; last E Street stage appearance, Bruce returned the favor when Social Distortion played Asbury Park&#8217;s Sea.Hear.Now. Festival in the autumn of 2018. Bruce took a rare rocking break from his Broadway schedule to join the band for three songs that night: the aforementioned &#8220;Misery Loves Company,&#8221; a terrific cover of &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/07/19/cover-me-ring-of-fire/\">Ring of Fire</a>,&#8221; and (of course) &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/imPrGD5RIT8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Bad Luck<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> April 16, 2009 (Los Angeles, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> September 30, 2018 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>An avid Social Distortion fan, Bruce was bound to cover their biggest hit. Watch Bruce team up&#8211;three times&#8211;with Mike Ness and Social Distortion on &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221; </p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
